I'd be into hybridizing these sandwiches a la the convention for the tail
end of a Playin in isolation.  That is, if we have "Playing Reprise"s (and
I think we probably should) why can't we also have "Cryptical Reprise"s,
"Uncle John's Reprise"s, etc?  By having a common modifier on the end of a
song's name for its tail-end-only appearance in a show (<song name>
Reprise) we can teach the search engine to ignore such instances as a
second rendition of a song in the same show (much in the same way that the
search engine can ignore song titles with the word "Jam" following them,
if we like).  Of course, this screws with searching for shows where *only*
a Playin Reprise occurs -- if we want to count such an instance as the
occurance of a Playing at that show, right?, unless we can say "don't
consider Playin Reprise as a second instance of Playin -- unless it's the
*only* instance of Playin in a show, in which case, count it as a Playin"
(which I guess is feasible). 


